<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Based on 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" form="inermis" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hystrix subsp. forma" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="hystrix" subSpecies="forma">Convolvulus hystrix forma inermis</taxonomicName>
Chiov.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distinguishing features">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distinguishing features.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Plant virtually unarmed, the side branches long, relatively slender, spinescent when old, short lateral branchlets absent or, when present, neither rigid nor spine-like. Indumentum and flower heads similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="subsp. hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="hystrix" subSpecies="hystrix">subsp. hystrix</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Bari and Nogol regions of NE Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Hansen &amp; Heemstra</emphasis>
6297, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Becket</emphasis>
687, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Nugent</emphasis>
33, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Hemming</emphasis>
1866).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Occasional specimens intermediate with subspecies 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vahl, Symb. Bot. 1: 16. 1790. (Vahl" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hystrix">hystrix</taxonomicName>
are known from the same region (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Lavranos &amp; Carter</emphasis>
24645, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Bally &amp; Melville</emphasis>
15450).
</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="130" lastPageNumber="131" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Two other specimens from NE Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">
<pageBreakToken pageId="130" pageNumber="131" start="start">Beckett</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
42, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Thulin et al</emphasis>
. 9488) are close to both 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Wood &amp; Williams &amp; Mitchell &amp; Carine &amp; Harris &amp; Scotland" authorityYear="2015" baseAuthorityName="J. R. I. Wood &amp; R. W. Scotland" baseAuthorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hystrix subsp. inermis" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="hystrix" subSpecies="inermis">Convolvulus hystrix subsp. inermis</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin, Nordic J. Bot. 23: 629. 2005. (Thulin" authorityYear="2005" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scopulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Convolvulus scopulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. They are similar in habit to both species but the stems and leaves are sericeous, the leaves oblong-lanceolate and the bracteoles similar to the leaves but acuminate to a fine point. They may represent an undescribed species or a form of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vahl, Symb. Bot. 1: 16. 1790. (Vahl" authorityYear="1790" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus hystrix" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Convolvulus hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thulin, Nordic J. Bot. 23: 629. 2005. (Thulin" authorityYear="2005" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus scopulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="130" pageNumber="131" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scopulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="130" pageNumber="131">Convolvulus scopulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
